Traineeship Description:
This position reports to the Global Marketing Director and interfaces with the company dept head and marketing staff. Taiger is committed to progressive growth at personal and professional levels with departmental rotation, leadership opportunities, and empowerment.

Specific Responsibilities:
Trainee to be involved in:

Execute and manage events
· Assist the marketing manager in events identification and evaluation
· Participate in brainstorming and implementing event plans and concepts
· End to end event management; timeline management, project management, materials development, logistics administration, event feedback surveys, post-event reporting
· Assist in negotiating sponsorship deals
· Updating/managing leads in CRM

Plan, execute and manage Taiger’s presence on Social Media
· Write, manage and oversee social media content across LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook, YouTube, and Instagram
· Develop and execute regular e-newsletter via Mailchimp and Hubspot to support lead generation and nurturing efforts
· Measure and report on the success of social media campaign
· Stay up to date with the latest social media best practices and technologies
· Work with outsourced copywriters and designers to ensure content is informative and appealing where necessary
· Collaborate with Marketing, Sales and Product Development teams
· Communicate with industry professionals and influencers via social media to create a strong network

Plan, execute and manage Taiger’s partner program initiatives
· Drive programs and initiatives with Partners to increase partner-created pipeline across all 3 product lines indicated by Partner Mgrs
· GTM execution &amp; integrated programs to key managed partners developed by Marketing Mgr
· Monthly program report of partner programs indicating current status/achievement to meet final KPI laid out by Marketing Mgr

Competencies:
· Experience in marketing especially in social media, events and communication
· Strong overall communication skills. Critical thinking and problem-solving skills.
· Ability to tell a story. Excellent writing ability
· Ability to write and/or design using Adobe and/or Canva software
· Good knowledge of key social media tools, best practices and KPIs
· Understanding of SEO and web traffic metrics

Education Qualifications Required for the Traineeship Role:&nbsp;
· BA/BSc in marketing, business or equivalent

Eligibility Criteria for SGUnitedTraineeships:
• Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident; and
a. Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); or
b. Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020.
